  "prompt": "What hotel in Ladakh would be safe for unmarried couples, without the harassment of police, hotel staff, and moral police?",
  "response": "Ladakh is generally a safe and welcoming destination for tourists, including unmarried couples. However, to ensure a comfortable and hassle-free stay, it\u2019s important to choose reputable hotels or guesthouses that are known for being couple-friendly. Here are some tips and suggestions:\n\n### Recommended Hotels in Ladakh for Unmarried Couples:\n1. **The Grand Dragon Ladakh (Leh)**  \n   - A luxury hotel with excellent service and a professional attitude towards all guests.  \n   - Known for respecting privacy and catering to international and domestic tourists.\n\n2. **Ladakh Sarai Resort (Leh)**  \n   - A boutique resort with a serene environment and ethical hospitality standards.  \n   - Couple-friendly and ensures privacy for guests.\n\n3. **The Zen Ladakh (Leh)**  \n   - A modern hotel with a welcoming atmosphere for all types of travelers.  \n   - Known for its courteous staff and privacy-conscious policies.\n\n4. **Chospa Hotel (Leh)**  \n   - A mid-range hotel with a relaxed and friendly vibe.  \n   - Popular among couples and backpackers.\n\n5. **Hotel Shaynam (Leh)**  \n   - Budget-friendly option with a no-nonsense approach to guest privacy.  \n   - Welcomes all kinds of travelers, including unmarried couples.\n\n---\n\n### Tips for a Safe and Comfortable Stay:\n1. **Book Reputable Hotels**: Choose well-reviewed hotels or guesthouses that explicitly state they are couple-friendly.  \n2. **Carry Valid IDs**: Both partners should carry government-issued IDs (like Aadhar card or passport) for check-in.  \n3. **Use Online Portals**: Platforms like **Booking.com**, **MakeMyTrip**, or **Airbnb** often list couple-friendly accommodations, and reviews can help you make an informed choice.  \n4. **Avoid Drama**: While most hotels in Ladakh are professional, it\u2019s best to avoid drawing unnecessary attention.  \n5. **Local Laws**: Be aware that Ladakh is a conservative region, so it\u2019s advisable to maintain decorum in public spaces to avoid unwanted attention.\n\nLadakh is a beautiful and peaceful destination, and with the right choice of accommodation, unmarried couples can enjoy a relaxing and safe stay without any issues.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
